        i "I grew up and studied IT and CS in India. After working in New Delhi for 2 years, I went to Carnegie Mellon to study Software Management. I joined Ibibo after CMU and worked as a PM, building mobile gaming and messaging products.  
      p
        i One of my projects as an RPM is Stickers for Facebook Messenger. Stickers are lighthearted and a delightful way to express yourself — it's great to see how emoji change the way people communicate!"
        .quote  -Garima Sinha, 2013 RPM  
    a.button.style2.down.anchored(href='#seven') Next

  //
     Dwight
  section#seven.main.style2.left.dark.fullscreen
    .content.box.interviewPage
      header
        h2 Bollywood Extra, Startup Founder, Facebook PM (yes, we’re serious) 
      p
        i "Before Facebook, I cofounded a used car search engine startup. We joined Y-Combinator, raised funding and captured 2% of the market before Facebook acquired us.
      p
        i I had no idea what I wanted to do after graduating, so I bought a one way ticket to India to become a reporter. In India, I ended up in a Bollywood movie, marched with Tibetan monks, photographed the Nepalese revolution, and worked with a Spanish film crew in Mongolia – but it turned out that I’m a really mediocre reporter."  
        .quote  -Dwight Crow, 2012 RPM   
